<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Major League Baseball=E2=80=99s rookies will w=
ear special patches on their jerseys as they make their big-league debuts, =
and they=E2=80=99re all destined for the collectibles market.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Topps, the trading-card company now owned by F=
anatics Inc., has aligned with MLB and the league=E2=80=99s union on the ne=
w program, which they=E2=80=99re billing as the first of its kind. It begin=
s at the season openers on Thursday.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When rookies are called up, they=E2=80=99ll we=
ar an extra patch opposite their sponsor sleeve for their first on-field ap=
pearance. After the game, the patch will be taken off, authenticated as gam=
